---
import PageLayout from "@/layouts/PageLayout.astro";
---

<PageLayout title="colophon - coredump" pageKind="colophon">
  <section class="colo">
    <div class="shell">
      <header class="colo__head">
        <div class="meta">colophon</div>
        <h1 class="colo__title">on this notebook.</h1>
        <p class="colo__lede">
          a manual for reading <em>coredump</em>. what it is, what it
          isn't, and what it's set in.
        </p>
      </header>

      <hr class="hairline-thick" />

      <div class="colo__body">
        <section class="colo__section">
          <pre class="colo__rubric">────[ I · WHAT THIS IS ]────────────────────────────</pre>
          <p>
            <em>coredump</em> is a writing surface for technical work that
            doesn't fit a tweet, a doc, or a slide. it lives at the layer
            below the framework: cache lines, system calls, kernel
            interfaces, lock-free state machines, time, latency, and the
            small physics of computers.
          </p>
          <p>
            entries are long when they need to be, terse when they don't.
            there is no posting schedule. there is no newsletter, no
            comment section, no analytics, and no tracking.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="colo__section">
          <pre class="colo__rubric">────[ II · NO AUTHOR ]──────────────────────────────</pre>
          <p>
            there is no author byline anywhere on this site, and there
            will not be one. the writing is first-person because all
            technical writing is, but the person is deliberately
            scrubbed from the page so the ideas can be argued with on
            their own terms.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="colo__section">
          <pre class="colo__rubric">────[ III · WHAT'S OUT OF SCOPE ]───────────────────</pre>
          <ul class="colo__list">
            <li>investment advice or market commentary of any kind</li>
            <li>trading strategies, instruments, venues, or P&L</li>
            <li>employment, hiring, or company-specific content</li>
            <li>discourse, vibes, hot takes, or industry drama</li>
            <li>tooling reviews where the tool ships in three months</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="colo__section">
          <pre class="colo__rubric">────[ IV · TYPE ]───────────────────────────────────</pre>
          <dl class="colo__typedl">
            <div>
              <dt>display + body</dt>
              <dd>
                <em>Fraunces</em>: variable opsz / wght / SOFT.
                set by Undercase Type, released under SIL OFL.
              </dd>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dt>ui + labels</dt>
              <dd>
                <em>Inter</em>: variable, set by Rasmus Andersson, SIL OFL.
              </dd>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dt>mono / code</dt>
              <dd>
                <em>JetBrains Mono</em>: variable, SIL OFL.
              </dd>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dt>sticky notes</dt>
              <dd>
                <em>Caveat</em>: by Pablo Impallari et al., SIL OFL.
              </dd>
            </div>
          </dl>
        </section>

        <section class="colo__section">
          <pre class="colo__rubric">────[ V · TECHNICAL ]───────────────────────────────</pre>
          <p>
            built with <a href="https://astro.build" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Astro</a>;
            mdx for content, shiki for syntax highlighting (with a
            black-and-white theme that uses italic and weight instead of
            colour), and one CSS file. no react. no client framework.
            the only javascript is the reading-progress bar, the UTC
            clock, and the keyboard handlers for the inspector and the
            phosphor mode.
          </p>
          <p>
            page weight target: under 80 kB on a fresh visit, font
            included, before any entry-specific assets.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="colo__section">
          <pre class="colo__rubric">────[ VI · SHORTCUTS ]──────────────────────────────</pre>
          <dl class="colo__kbd">
            <div><dt>g</dt><dd>baseline-grid overlay</dd></div>
            <div><dt>?</dt><dd>shortcut sheet</dd></div>
            <div><dt>esc</dt><dd>close sheet</dd></div>
            <div><dt>↑↑↓↓←→←→ba</dt><dd>phosphor mode</dd></div>
          </dl>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</PageLayout>

<style>
  .colo {
    padding-block: 3rem 4rem;
    /* Prevent any child from blowing out the viewport width */
    overflow-x: hidden;
    max-width: 100vw;
  }
  .colo__head {
    padding-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }
  .colo__title {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-variation-settings: "opsz" 144, "wght" 280, "SOFT" 30;
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 7vw, 5rem);
    line-height: 0.95;
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem;
  }
  .colo__lede {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    max-width: 44ch;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .colo__body {
    display: grid;
    gap: 3.5rem;
    padding-block: 3rem 0;
    max-width: min(44rem, 100%);
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    line-height: 1.62;
  }
  .colo__section {
    min-width: 0;
  }
  .colo__section p + p {
    margin-top: 1em;
  }
  .colo__section p {
    margin: 0;
  }
  .colo__rubric {
    margin: 0 0 1.2rem;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    line-height: 1;
    white-space: pre;
    max-width: 100%;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  @media (max-width: 36rem) {
    .colo__rubric {
      /* Hide the decorative ASCII tail — only show the label part */
      white-space: nowrap;
      overflow: hidden;
      text-overflow: clip;
      /* Shrink font slightly so the label itself never wraps */
      font-size: 0.65rem;
    }
  }
  .colo__list {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    list-style: none;
  }
  .colo__list li {
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 1.6rem;
    margin-top: 0.4rem;
  }
  .colo__list li::before {
    content: "-";
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-muted);
  }
  .colo__typedl,
  .colo__kbd {
    margin: 0;
    display: grid;
    gap: 1rem;
  }
  .colo__typedl > div,
  .colo__kbd > div {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 9rem 1fr;
    gap: 1rem;
  }
  .colo__typedl dt,
  .colo__kbd dt {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    padding-top: 0.3em;
  }
  .colo__typedl dd,
  .colo__kbd dd {
    margin: 0;
  }
  .colo__kbd dt {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    text-transform: none;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }
  .colo__section a {
    color: var(--color-ink);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-ink);
  }
  .colo__section a:hover {
    background: var(--color-ink);
    color: var(--color-paper);
  }

  @media (max-width: 48rem) {
    .colo__typedl > div,
    .colo__kbd > div {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 0.2rem;
    }
  }
</style>
